test for restoring both M7 and M8 after being turned off in a sub
with M73 autorestore set

Re-expressed NGC-only for gomc: M73 auto-restore is a pure interpreter feature;
the classic test's only Python was two `;py,assert this.params["_mist"/"_flood"]`
lines. gomc removed the embedded Python interpreter, so the restored state is now
surfaced with a `(debug, _mist=#<_mist> _flood=#<_flood>)` comment and confirmed by
the MIST_ON/FLOOD_ON calls that reappear in the canon trace after the sub returns.
Runs under the standalone rs274 interpreter like its m73autorestore.0 sibling.
